      "content": "While it's true that honey has some adhesive properties, using it as a makeshift glue is not advisable. A gaping wound can lead to further complications, including infection and impaired healing. Instead, gently clean the wound with water, apply a thin layer of manuka honey, and then cover it with a sterile bandage. If the wound edges are still wide, you may need to use a sterile gauze pad to help bring them closer together. Keep an eye on the wound for any signs of infection, and if it doesn't improve or if you experience increased pain, swelling, or redness, it's important to seek medical attention. Remember, it's always better to err on the side of caution when it comes to wounds.",
